view-less" style="display:none">View less</span></button></div></div>




<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ultimate-guide-to-energy-bites"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="ultimate_guide_to_energy_bites"></span>Ultimate guide to Energy Bites!<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>These energy balls are no bake, super easy to make and take less than 10 minutes to put together. Loaded with protein, fiber and healthy fats to keep you full and loaded with energy throughout the day. The base of this recipe is only a couple of ingredients: peanut butter, old fashioned oats, flax seed and honey.&nbsp;Next you pick your favorite add in&rsquo;s. Keep it simple and do chocolate chips or add in M &amp; M&rsquo;s, chocolate or even lemon! Everything gets combined in one bowl. Best of all you never have to turn on the oven!</p>



<p>You may have heard of these referred to as energy balls, lactation bites or protein bites. Either way they are a healthy pick me up that is the perfect on the go snack to give you energy throughout the day.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image is-resized"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[8][self::FIGURE]/*[1][self::IMG]" decoding="async" width="665" height="932" data-pin-url="https://chefsavvy.com/5-ingredient-peanut-butter-energy-bites/?tp_image_id=31592" data-pin-id="835980749563296231" data-pin-description="These no bake Peanut Butter Energy Bites are a healthy, protein packed snack made with just 5 ingredients and ready in 10 minutes! Nutritious, wholesome, and made with simple real food ingredients, these gluten free energy bites are perfect for an on-the-go breakfast, afternoon snack, or post-workout treat. #energybites #healthysnacks #glutenfree #nobake #snacks" data-pin-title="Energy Bites (8 Flavors!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;665&#039;%20height=&#039;932&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20665%20932&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="5 Ingredient Peanut Butter Energy Bites in white bowl" class="wp-image-31592 perfmatters-lazy" style="width:755px;height:1058px" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-energy-balls.jpg" data-srcset="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-energy-balls.jpg 665w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-energy-balls-300x420.jpg 300w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-energy-balls-640x897.jpg 640w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-energy-balls-400x561.jpg 400w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-energy-balls-560x785.jpg 560w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 705px) calc(100vw - 40px), 665px" /></figure>


<div class="featuredcomment notop nobot">
        <div class="fc-rating">
        <svg class="cicon icon-star-solid"><title>star</title><use xlink:href="#icon-star-solid"></use></svg><svg class="cicon icon-star-solid"><title>star</title><use xlink:href="#icon-star-solid"></use></svg><svg class="cicon icon-star-solid"><title>star</title><use xlink:href="#icon-star-solid"></use></svg><svg class="cicon icon-star-solid"><title>star</title><use xlink:href="#icon-star-solid"></use></svg><svg class="cicon icon-star-solid"><title>star</title><use xlink:href="#icon-star-solid"></use></svg>    </div>
        <p>&ldquo;These are amazing! I make these balls all the time because I&rsquo;m that obsessed with peanut butter. Always switching up the ingredients to give it a new kick &#128578;&rdquo; &ndash; Karen</p>
</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-why-you-ll-love-these-energy-balls"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="why_youll_love_these_energy_balls"></span>Why you&rsquo;ll love these energy balls<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>The best things about this energy bites recipe is that it is super versatile. If you do not have flax seed on hand substitute wheat germ. Try dark chocolate chips instead of semi-sweet. Add in shredded coconut, cranberries or cocoa powder.</p>



<p>These Peanut Butter Energy Bites could easily pass as dessert. My batch lasted less than 24 hours. They are the perfect mix between a granola bar and cookie dough. Great to curb the afternoon munchies and the dreaded mid afternoon energy slump. If your craving chocolate try my <a href="https://chefsavvy.com/chocolate-peanut-butter-energy-bites/">Chocolate Peanut Butter Energy Bites!</a></p>



<p>You can even freeze these oatmeal energy bites if you don&rsquo;t eat them all within a week. Here&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;ll need to make these No Bake Energy Bites:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[14][self::FIGURE]/*[1][self::IMG]" decoding="async" width="820" height="470" data-pin-url="https://chefsavvy.com/5-ingredient-peanut-butter-energy-bites/?tp_image_id=66533" data-pin-description="These no bake Peanut Butter Energy Bites are a healthy, protein packed snack made with just 5 ingredients and ready in 10 minutes! Nutritious, wholesome, and made with simple real food ingredients, these gluten free energy bites are perfect for an on-the-go breakfast, afternoon snack, or post-workout treat. #energybites #healthysnacks #glutenfree #nobake #snacks" data-pin-title="Energy Bites (8 Flavors!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;820&#039;%20height=&#039;470&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20820%20470&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="overhead shot of energy ball ingredients on counter" class="wp-image-66533 perfmatters-lazy" style="width:820px;height:470px" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-820x470.jpg" data-srcset="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-820x470.jpg 820w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-1080x618.jpg 1080w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-767x439.jpg 767w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-400x229.jpg 400w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-1480x847.jpg 1480w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-300x172.jpg 300w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-768x440.jpg 768w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-1536x879.jpg 1536w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-560x321.jpg 560w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls-150x86.jpg 150w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/ingredients-for-energy-balls.jpg 1640w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 780px) calc(100vw - 40px), 740px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredients"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="ingredients"></span>Ingredients<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-checks">
<li><strong>Creamy Peanut Butter:</strong> Helps to bind the energy bites together. You can also use your favorite nut butter as well!</li>



<li><strong>Semi Sweet Chocolate Chips:</strong> I love using mini chocolate chips if I have them on hand. Dark chocolate chunks are also amazing in this!</li>



<li><strong>Old Fashioned Oats:</strong> I prefer to use old fashioned oats or rolled oats in this recipe. I would not recommend making these with steel cut oats or instant oats. If you want to keep these bites gluten free make sure to use certified gluten free oats!</li>



<li><strong>Ground Flax Seed:</strong> Adds a boost of fiber and nutrients. If you don&rsquo;t have flax seed on hand substitute hemp seed, chia seed or add extra old fashioned oats.</li>



<li><strong>Honey:</strong> Adds the perfect amount of sweetness to these energy balls. Agave can be used in place of the honey.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image is-resized"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[17][self::FIGURE]/*[1][self::IMG]" decoding="async" width="665" height="823" data-pin-url="https://chefsavvy.com/5-ingredient-peanut-butter-energy-bites/?tp_image_id=31593" data-pin-id="835980749563296231" data-pin-description="These no bake Peanut Butter Energy Bites are a healthy, protein packed snack made with just 5 ingredients and ready in 10 minutes! Nutritious, wholesome, and made with simple real food ingredients, these gluten free energy bites are perfect for an on-the-go breakfast, afternoon snack, or post-workout treat. #energybites #healthysnacks #glutenfree #nobake #snacks" data-pin-title="Energy Bites (8 Flavors!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;665&#039;%20height=&#039;823&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20665%20823&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="peanut butter protein ball Ingredients in white bowl" class="wp-image-31593 perfmatters-lazy" style="width:768px;height:951px" title="No Bake Peanut Butter Energy Bite Ingredients in white bowl" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/easy-energy-balls.jpg" data-srcset="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/easy-energy-balls.jpg 665w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/easy-energy-balls-400x495.jpg 400w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/easy-energy-balls-560x693.jpg 560w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/easy-energy-balls-300x371.jpg 300w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/easy-energy-balls-640x792.jpg 640w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 705px) calc(100vw - 40px), 665px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-chefsavvy-heading-with-icon heading-icon"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="how_to_make_energy_balls"></span><span class="hicon"><svg class="cicon icon-question" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#icon-question"></use></svg></span><span>How to make Energy Balls</span><span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>To make these peanut butter chocolate chip energy bites simply combine all 5 ingredients in a medium bowl. Stir to combine. Place in the refrigerator for 15-30 minutes so they are easier to roll. Roll into 12 bites and store in the fridge for up to a week.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image is-resized"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[20][self::FIGURE]/*[1][self::IMG]" decoding="async" width="665" height="871" data-pin-url="https://chefsavvy.com/5-ingredient-peanut-butter-energy-bites/?tp_image_id=31591" data-pin-id="835980749563296231" data-pin-description="These no bake Peanut Butter Energy Bites are a healthy, protein packed snack made with just 5 ingredients and ready in 10 minutes! Nutritious, wholesome, and made with simple real food ingredients, these gluten free energy bites are perfect for an on-the-go breakfast, afternoon snack, or post-workout treat. #energybites #healthysnacks #glutenfree #nobake #snacks" data-pin-title="Energy Bites (8 Flavors!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;665&#039;%20height=&#039;871&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20665%20871&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="No bake peanut butter protein bites in a white bowl" class="wp-image-31591 perfmatters-lazy" style="width:764px;height:1001px" title="No bake energy balls in a white bowl" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/chocolate-chip-energy-balls.jpg" data-srcset="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/chocolate-chip-energy-balls.jpg 665w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/chocolate-chip-energy-balls-400x524.jpg 400w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/chocolate-chip-energy-balls-560x733.jpg 560w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/chocolate-chip-energy-balls-300x393.jpg 300w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/chocolate-chip-energy-balls-640x838.jpg 640w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 705px) calc(100vw - 40px), 665px" /></figure>


		<div class="contentbox contentbox-black-marble mainsection">
		<div class="contentbox-a notop nobot">
			

<h3 class="wp-block-chefsavvy-heading-with-icon heading-icon"><span class="hicon"><svg class="cicon icon-lightbulb" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#icon-lightbulb"></use></svg></span><span>Tips for making energy bites</span></h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-circles">
<li>Always try rolling the bites after they have been refrigerated. This makes rolling them so much easier. If you are still having trouble rolling them try wetting your hands or adding 1 or 2 tablespoons of water to the mixture.</li>



<li>Instead of rolling out into balls the mixture can be placed in a square baking dish lined with parchment paper. Refrigerate and cut to make no bake energy bars!</li>
</ul>

		</div>
		</div>		
		


<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[22][self::FIGURE]/*[1][self::IMG]" decoding="async" width="820" height="699" data-pin-url="https://chefsavvy.com/5-ingredient-peanut-butter-energy-bites/?tp_image_id=66716" data-pin-description="These no bake Peanut Butter Energy Bites are a healthy, protein packed snack made with just 5 ingredients and ready in 10 minutes! Nutritious, wholesome, and made with simple real food ingredients, these gluten free energy bites are perfect for an on-the-go breakfast, afternoon snack, or post-workout treat. #energybites #healthysnacks #glutenfree #nobake #snacks" data-pin-title="Energy Bites (8 Flavors!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;820&#039;%20height=&#039;699&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20820%20699&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="overhead shot of four different energy ball flavors" class="wp-image-66716 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-820x699.jpg" data-srcset="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-820x699.jpg 820w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-1080x920.jpg 1080w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-767x653.jpg 767w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-400x341.jpg 400w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-1480x1261.jpg 1480w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-300x256.jpg 300w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-768x654.jpg 768w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-1536x1308.jpg 1536w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-560x477.jpg 560w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1-150x128.jpg 150w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-ball-variations-in-bowl-1.jpg 1640w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 780px) calc(100vw - 40px), 740px" /></figure>


		<div class="contentbox contentbox-black mainsection">
		<div class="contentbox-a notop nobot">
			

<h3 class="wp-block-chefsavvy-heading-with-icon heading-icon"><span class="hicon"><svg class="cicon icon-right-left" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#icon-right-left"></use></svg></span><span>Energy ball variations</span></h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-circles">
<li><strong>White Chocolate Cranberry</strong>: Add in white chocolate chips and dried cranberries!</li>



<li><a href="https://chefsavvy.com/chocolate-peanut-butter-energy-bites/">Double Chocolate Energy Bites</a>: Add some cocoa powder and chocolate chips (I like adding dark chocolate chips)</li>



<li><strong>Almond Joy</strong>: Replace some of the oats for chopped almonds, coconut and of course chocolate chips!</li>



<li><strong><a href="https://chefsavvy.com/oatmeal-raisin-energy-bites/">Cinnamon Raisin Energy Balls</a>:</strong> Instead of chocolate chips adding in raisin and some cinnamon.</li>



<li><strong>Trail Mix: </strong>Loaded with chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.</li>



<li><strong>Monster Cookies:</strong> Add in mini M &amp; M&rsquo;s and chocolate chips! This is my kids favorite version!</li>



<li><strong>Lemon:</strong> Zest one whole lemon then add then juice half of it! Sprinkle in poppy seeds too!</li>



<li><strong><a href="https://chefsavvy.com/birthday-cake-energy-balls/">Birthday Cake Energy Balls</a>: </strong>This is my favorite! Made with sprinkles and vanilla protein powder it tastes just like birthday cake!</li>
</ul>

		</div>
		</div>		
		


<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[24][self::FIGURE]/*[1][self::IMG]" decoding="async" width="820" height="706" data-pin-url="https://chefsavvy.com/5-ingredient-peanut-butter-energy-bites/?tp_image_id=66717" data-pin-description="These no bake Peanut Butter Energy Bites are a healthy, protein packed snack made with just 5 ingredients and ready in 10 minutes! Nutritious, wholesome, and made with simple real food ingredients, these gluten free energy bites are perfect for an on-the-go breakfast, afternoon snack, or post-workout treat. #energybites #healthysnacks #glutenfree #nobake #snacks" data-pin-title="Energy Bites (8 Flavors!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;820&#039;%20height=&#039;706&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20820%20706&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="overhead shot of 4 flavor combinations for energy balls" class="wp-image-66717 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-820x706.jpg" data-srcset="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-820x706.jpg 820w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-1080x930.jpg 1080w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-767x660.jpg 767w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-400x344.jpg 400w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-1480x1274.jpg 1480w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-300x258.jpg 300w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-768x661.jpg 768w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-1536x1322.jpg 1536w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-560x482.jpg 560w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl-150x129.jpg 150w, https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/uploads/energy-bite-variations-in-bowl.jpg 1640w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 780px) calc(100vw - 40px), 740px" /></figure>


