<h3 class="wp-block-chefsavvy-heading-with-icon heading-icon"><span>Energy Bites FAQ</span></h3>


		<div class="togglelist notop nobot">
			

			<div class="toggleitem" id="faqitem-can-you-freeze-energy-bites">
				<h2 tabindex="0" role="button" class="wp-block-heading" id="h-can-you-freeze-energy-bites"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="can_you_freeze_energy_bites"></span>Can you freeze energy bites?<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>				<div class="togglereveal notop nobot">
					



<p>Yes! These no bake energy bites can be frozen in an airtight container for up to 3 months!</p>


				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="toggleitem" id="faqitem-what-can-i-use-instead-of-flax-seed">
				<h2 tabindex="0" role="button" class="wp-block-heading" id="h-what-can-i-use-instead-of-flax-seed"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="what_can_i_use_instead_of_flax_seed"></span>What can I use instead of flax seed?<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>				<div class="togglereveal notop nobot">
					



<p>Chia seed or hemp seed are a good alternative to ground flax seed. You can also substitute the flax for more oats or unsweetened shredded coconut!</p>


				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="toggleitem" id="faqitem-would-maple-syrup-work">
				<h2 tabindex="0" role="button" class="wp-block-heading" id="h-would-maple-syrup-work"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="would_maple_syrup_work"></span>Would Maple syrup work?<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>				<div class="togglereveal notop nobot">
					



<p>Yes! Maple syrup can be used in place of the honey!</p>


				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="toggleitem" id="faqitem-what-are-the-calories-per-serving">
				<h2 tabindex="0" role="button" class="wp-block-heading" id="h-what-are-the-calories-per-serving"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="what_are_the_calories_per_serving"></span>What are the calories per serving?<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>				<div class="togglereveal notop nobot">
					



<p>This is a question that gets asked a lot. The calories are 200 for 1 serving (1 bite) I know that seems like a lot but the peanut butter in this really adds to the calories. These bites are perfect as a snack or pick me up or a quick breakfast before working out! Some readers have tried using <a href="https://amzn.to/3sxGo9u" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener" target="_blank">powdered peanut butter</a> to save on calories!</p>


				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="toggleitem" id="faqitem-what-do-i-do-if-its-too-dry">
				<h2 tabindex="0" role="button" class="wp-block-heading" id="h-what-do-i-do-if-its-too-dry"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="what_do_i_do_if_its_too_dry"></span>What do I do if its too dry?<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>				<div class="togglereveal notop nobot">
					



<p>If the mixture seems too dry try adding a splash of water. I do 1 tablespoon at a time. This helps bind everything together. Alternatively you can always add a scoop more of peanut butter, honey or maple syrup to bind everything up!</p>
				</div>
			</div>
					</div>
		
		</div>
		</div>		
		


