	<li class="comment-li">
		<article id="comment-595295" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 comdiv">
			<div class="comavatar"></div>
			<div class="comright">
				<div class="commeta">
					<h3 class="comauth">Kathy V</h3>
					<div class="comdate"><time datetime="2025-10-15T22:16:19+00:00">October 15, 2025</time></div>
					<div class="comrating"><img data-od-unknown-tag data-od-xpath="/HTML/BODY/MAIN[@id=&amp;apos;body&amp;apos;]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[3][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::UL]/*[3][self::LI]/*[1][self::ARTICLE]/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]/*[3][self::DIV]/*[1][self::IMG]" class="wprm-comment-rating perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;80&#039;%20height=&#039;16&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%2080%2016&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="4 stars" width="80" height="16" data-src="https://chefsavvy.com/wp-content/themes/chefsavvy2024/images/stars-4.svg" />
</div>				</div>		
				<div class="comcontent notop nobot">
					<p>Made 3 flavors of these today. Even after chilling and wetting my hands, they were still a bit hard to make into balls (crumbly). I tried adding a bit of water to crumbs (didn&rsquo;t really work). Added a small bit of (vegan) milk into second batch&mdash;that seemed to work better. Still took a while to mold into balls, but eventually worked out. Made them for my daughter and son in-law. I&rsquo;m sure they&rsquo;ll love them.</p>
				</div>				
								
				<div class="comactions">
					<ul>
						<li class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-595295" data-commentid="595295" data-postid="6660" data-belowelement="comment-595295" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathy V" aria-label="Reply to Kathy V">Reply</a></li>					</ul>
				</div>
							</div>
		</article>
<ul class="children">
	<li class="comment-li">
		<article id="comment-595644" class="comment byuser comment-author-chef-savvy bypostauthor even depth-2 comdiv byadmin">
			<div class="comavatar"></div>
			<div class="comright">
				<div class="commeta">
					<h3 class="comauth">Kelley Simmons</h3>
					<div class="comdate"><time datetime="2025-10-18T13:47:52+00:00">October 18, 2025</time></div>
									</div>		
				<div class="comcontent notop nobot">
					<p>Sorry to hear this wasn&rsquo;t coming together for you Kathy! Did you try refrigerating for a bit? That does help. If it&rsquo;s still crumbly I add in a bit more peanut butter or honey to help bind everything. Hope this helps and your daughter and son in law enjoy!</p>
				</div>				
							</div>
		</article>
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
